Lab Architecture

The SOC laboratory environment consisted of the following components:
Kali Linux — acting as the attacker simulation machine.
Windows 10 endpoint — acting as the monitored target system.
Wazuh SIEM — collecting and analyzing security events.

Log sources and network recon 

Network reconnaissance was performed using Nmap, revealing open ports 135 (MSRPC), 139 (NetBIOS), and 445 (SMB) on the Windows target.
The presence of SMB on port 445 indicated a potential attack surface for enumeration and credential-based attacks.
This finding guided further investigation using tools like enum4linux, smbclient, and Hydra.

